.container
  %p.lead.spacer Lita is a chat bot written in Ruby. It connects with your favorite chat service and helps keep you efficient while having fun.

  .row.spacer.text-c
    .col-md-4
      %h3
        .icon-lg.glyphicon.glyphicon-fast-forward
        Automate tasks
      Turn tedious, time-consuming, and error-prone tasks into simple commands.
    .col-md-4
      %h3
        .icon-lg.glyphicon.glyphicon-eye-open
        Provide visibility
      Using chat as the primary interface for business operations lets everyone see what's happening all the time.
    .col-md-4
      %h3
        .icon-lg.glyphicon.glyphicon-user
        Build a culture
      Having fun with your robot forms bonds and develops a sense of community.

  .row.spacer
    .col-md-3
      %h4
        .icon-lg.glyphicon.glyphicon-heart
        Built with Ruby
      Lita is written in <a href="https://www.ruby-lang.org/">Ruby</a>, a powerful, easy to learn programming language.
    .col-md-3
      %h4
        .icon-lg.glyphicon.glyphicon-gift
        Free and open source
      Lita is free to use and the source code is available on <a href="https://github.com/jimmycuadra/lita">GitHub</a>.
    .col-md-3
      %h4
        .icon-lg.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok-sign
        Pick your chat service
      Lita works with any chat service, including IRC, HipChat, and Campfire.
    .col-md-3
      %h4
        .icon-lg.glyphicon.glyphicon-wrench
        Extend with plugins
      Install <a href="https://plugins.lita.io/">plugins</a> from those already published, or write your own.
